The paper presents an approach to solving planning and scheduling problems using Answer Set Programming, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with modeling the domain using an action language, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper involves reasoning about constraints, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper deals with solving complex problems, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with scheduling, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
